The paper deals with anonymization techniques for set-valued datasets, which are commonly used in database management (cs.DB). The paper also addresses privacy concerns and proposes a new technique to overcome them (cs.CR). The proposed technique involves partial suppression, which is a common technique in machine learning and data mining (cs.LG). The paper also involves clustering and bucketization, which are common techniques in data science and data analysis (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses experiments and results, which are common in information retrieval (cs.IR).
